The paper deals with local graph clustering, which is a subfield of machine learning and data mining. The statistical perspective and analysis of the performance of a specific method (l1-regularized PageRank) suggest that the paper belongs to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. However, the use of random models and the computational perspective also suggest that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the analysis of the solution path and the use of optimization techniques suggest that the paper could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories.
